  {
    q: "Can you service the entire outdoor kitchen on one visit?",
    a: "Yes, and on a Malibu dispatch this is how we prefer to work. Grill, side burner, outdoor refrigerator, ice maker, kegerator, and rotisserie covered in a single service window. The reason matters: Malibu drive time from our Los Angeles branch runs 40 to 75 minutes each way depending on PCH traffic, and stacking a multi-appliance call means we bring the right parts inventory once instead of returning twice. We pre-confirm models on the phone (Lynx L54PSR, Alfresco ALXE-56, Twin Eagles TEBQ36R, Sub-Zero DEL3050, Marvel ML24RAS, Perlick HP24RS) so the truck rolls with the burner assemblies, igniter modules, gas valves, and refrigeration parts most commonly needed for those specific platforms."
