    a: "Probably not the entire system. On Lynx Professional grills like the L54PSR or L36PSR, total ignition failure usually traces to one of three things, and we work them in order from cheapest to most expensive. First: the battery in the spark module, Lynx uses a single AA on most professional builds and salt-air condensation accelerates battery drain; about a quarter of 'no spark' calls in Malibu resolve at the battery for under $20. Second: moisture in the spark module housing itself, water intrusion through a cracked seal lets salt corrode the contact points; we open it, dry it, treat it, sometimes replace the module ($180 to $280 installed). Third: corroded electrode tips, the actual spark electrodes near each burner pit and lose gap geometry over time; replacement is straightforward but you typically replace all of them at once because if one is gone the others are close behind. We diagnose in that order so you don't pay for parts you don't need."
