  },
  {
    q: "How often should a Malibu outdoor kitchen be serviced?",
    a: "Every six months on the coastal stretch, Carbon Beach, Malibu Colony, Broad Beach, Point Dume, anything within roughly half a mile of the Pacific. Inland Malibu (the canyon homes off Latigo, Encinal, and parts of Malibu Cove) can run on annual service. The coastal calendar covers: condenser coil cleaning on the outdoor refrigerator (salt-and-dust paste fouls coils 3x faster than inland), igniter electrode inspection and contact-point cleaning on the grill, burner port flush (salt deposits narrow the orifices), gas valve and regulator function check, drain inspection on the refrigerator, and a visual corrosion sweep on cabinet hardware. Catching salt-driven wear at the maintenance interval is roughly four times cheaper than waiting for the failure call. A $320 maintenance visit prevents a $680 burner-and-igniter rebuild."
  },
  {
    q: "What does outdoor kitchen repair cost in Malibu?",
    a: "Diagnostic is $120 and applies toward the repair when you approve work. Typical Malibu jobs: igniter module or electrode replacement $180 to $280 on most premium platforms; single burner assembly $280 to $480 (higher on Twin Eagles and Alfresco due to OEM parts pricing); gas valve replacement $320 to $580; outdoor refrigerator compressor work $480 to $880 on Sub-Zero, less on Marvel and U-Line outdoor; full burner-and-igniter rebuild on a 36-inch grill $580 to $980; ice maker mineral and salt buildup service $220 to $380; coastal preventive maintenance visit $280 to $420 covering the full outdoor kitchen suite. Premium-brand parts uplift is real, the same igniter module on a Twin Eagles TEBQ54R can run 30 to 50 percent above the equivalent on a mid-tier brand. We give written estimates before any work begins."
  },
  {
    q: "Do you carry parts for Lynx, Alfresco, Twin Eagles, and DCS on the truck?",
    a: "We carry the highest-volume coastal failure items on the truck for all four brands: igniter modules, electrode kits, single burner assemblies for the most common 36-inch and 54-inch builds, gas valve assemblies for Lynx Professional and Alfresco ALXE platforms, control knob and shaft kits, and rotisserie motors. Less common parts, full control panel assemblies, sealed-system refrigeration components on Sub-Zero outdoor units, specialty Twin Eagles burner builds, come through OEM authorized distribution with a 2 to 4 day lead. On the diagnostic visit we identify the part, give you a written quote, and if it's a stocked item we usually finish the same day. Malibu drive time means we plan ahead so you don't pay for two trips."
  },
