    q: "Should I cover my outdoor kitchen at the end of summer?",
    a: "Yes, with the caveat that the cover needs to be a breathable, properly fitted, brand-matched cover, not a generic vinyl tarp. Trapped moisture under a non-breathable cover does more damage than no cover at all in coastal exposure: condensation forms under the cover, salt accumulates in the trapped humidity, and corrosion accelerates inside what was supposed to be protection. Brand-matched covers from Lynx, Alfresco, and Twin Eagles use breathable marine-grade fabric with proper venting. We also recommend running the grill on high for 10 minutes before covering, the residual heat drives off surface moisture so the cover starts dry. Off-season (November through March in Malibu), monthly inspection under the cover catches early corrosion before it spreads."
