    <p class="section-number">07, Where we go in Malibu</p>
    <h2 class="section-title">Malibu neighborhoods we cover.</h2>

    <p>Malibu coverage runs the full PCH corridor from the Malibu Colony through Carbon Beach, La Costa Beach, Las Tunas Beach, Big Rock, Las Flores, and Topanga Beach on the south side, out through Point Dume, Zuma Beach, Broad Beach, and El Pescador on the north end, and up the canyons, Malibu Canyon, Latigo Canyon, Encinal Canyon, and Decker Canyon, into the inland portions of Malibu Cove and the Santa Monica Mountains.</p>

    <p>The microclimate matters to the service calendar. <strong>Carbon Beach</strong> and the immediate <strong>Malibu Colony</strong> frontage are the most aggressive coastal exposure on the territory; salt deposition rates run at the high end of what we see anywhere in Greater Los Angeles. <strong>Point Dume</strong> homes on the bluff edge see similar exposure plus more wind, which drives salt particles deeper into electrical compartments. <strong>Broad Beach</strong> is comparable to Carbon for direct beachfront and slightly less aggressive a few hundred feet inland. <strong>Malibu Cove</strong> and the canyon homes see substantially lower salt exposure, equipment there can run on annual rather than biannual service.</p>

    <p>Drive time from our LA branch to a Malibu address runs 40 to 75 minutes depending on PCH traffic and the specific destination. We schedule Malibu morning slots when possible (before PCH backs up) and we stack multi-appliance Malibu calls into longer windows so a single dispatch covers the full outdoor kitchen suite. Same-day availability on Malibu calls is realistic on most weekdays and during off-peak weekends; summer Saturdays during PCH peak we often book to next-business-day to ensure we arrive with the right parts and adequate time on-site.</p>
  </div>
</section>

